name: Live in Nashville (2010)
description:
This is Jason's fourth independently released project.  Listen as Jason and his band get down at the historic Ryman Auditorium.

Track Listing:
1. A Change is Gonna Come
2. Everybody...Nobody
3. Get Together Intro
4. Get Together
5. No Place Like...(Interlude)
6. Home
7. Good Friends and Stolen Songs (Interlude)
8. All That is You
9. Love Grows Old
10. Websites, CDs, and Diapers (Interlude)
11. Jay's Song
12. The Music

Personnel:
Jason Eskridge: Vocals and Guitar
Alex Petrounov: Guitars
Elijah Holt: Drums
Mike Majett: Bass
Dwan Hill: Keys
Darnell Levine: Backing Vocals
Missi Hale: Backing Vocals

Recorded by: Mike Ronkainen
Produced by: Jason Eskridge and Andrew Ramsey
Mixed and Mastered by: Andrew Ramsey
Photography by: Jason Jefferson
Artwork by: Darnell Levine

name: A Rustic Soul Christmas (2006)
description:
This is Jason's first studio project.  It was recorded in the fall of 2006.  This project is a collection of some of Jason's favorite Christmas songs. Jason and some of his most talented friends offer up warm renditions of five holiday standards plus a bonus track.

Track Listing
1. Little Drummer Boy
2. Silent Night
3. Have Yourself A Merry Little Christmas
4. O, Holy Night
5. We Wish You A Merry Christmas
6. Children Go Where I Send Thee (Hidden Track)

name: A Rustic Soul Christmas - 5 Pack
description: Get 5 A Rustic Soul Christmas CD's for one low price.  They make great stocking stuffers!
